# Key errors
E12000 = The key does not exist.
E12001 = The key has been revoked.
E12002 = Unsupported key algorithm: { $algorithm }.
E12003 = The certificate must be a valid PEM-encoded X.509 certificate.
E12004 = The key type is not valid for this operation.
E12005 = A certificate can only be attached to an asymmetric key.
E12006 = Failed to generate public JWK bindings for the key.
E12007 = Failed to serialize public JWK bindings for the key.
